My Formula is pretty simple.<br>
<br>
Before I go into the formula (which many of you I am sure will think is oversimplistic ) Let me define Succesful as being 'Rich and High level&quot; a guy to be envied because of all the phat lewt.<br>
<br>
1-Attendance - You are there for all the raids.  You are there on your brothers wedding day! Every time we log on you are there. The guy who scores high in attendance had full planer over a year and a half ago and had spent 100+hours in the planes proly. Plus went on most/all of the naggy and vox raids in the old days.Muliply this by 5 as the single most important attribute. These are GENERALLY the guys who get to 60 first and have all the coolest stuff first even if they don't have a lot of the other two attibutes.<br>
<br>
2- Affability - Ok here is a really important one. Some very rare individuals are so high on this scale that they can 'almost' do without number one!.They are so well liked by friends that when they don't have time to play thier friends log on as them an plvl for them!!!  This attribute means you are generally well liked. Dosen't mean you have a great personality or anything. Your sour pussed dour personality can win this one. It's all about character  I guess. I mean get real people who spend a huge portion of thier lives online generally don't have the greatest personalities in RL. We have this huge semi disfunctional family online that has it's own rating system. RL rules do not always apply.<br>
<br>
3- Ability - Being a good player. Lots of good players out there. Lots of bad ones too. However if you can score mediocre in this area and you have either a lot of time to play or are well liked and have lots of friends, then you can get by without much here.<br>
<br>
The formula is simple. <br>
<br>
1.If you aren't on you can't get the phat lewt and can't level a lot. It (generally) dosen't matter how well liked you are or how great a player you are.<br>
<br>
2. If you aren't at least liked a little even if you have a lot of the first attribute it can be hard to be a fast leveler and raid participant(Hard to go on a raid if no-one will invite you).But there are enough people of good skill to let your less than uber skills 'ride' on thier superior ones. You may have to take some extra chiding from time to time but heeh...<br>
<br>
3.Ability is dead last. Lots of people with ability and even more people with the 'potential' for ability. Some people definitely 'get it' sooner than others, but the game is group oriented and in most groups three or four fully contributing group members can carry the group (I know I carry sleeping group members pretty frequently).In the end game you mostly need to be able to respond and listen to directions. If the US army can get 1000's of high school drop outs to do that, desire can get most of the high school dropouts playing ths game to do this. That's why pick up naggy raids work, cause those in the know can lead the clueless to victory. Funny fact of life.<br>
<br>
